Detailed Description

The effect descriptor contains information on a particular effect implemented in the audio framework.

Class constructor.

The effect descriptor contains information on a particular effect implemented in the audio framework:

  • type: String corresponding to the OpenSL ES interface implemented by this effect
  • uuid: String for this particular implementation
  • connectMode: AudioEffect#EFFECT_INSERT, AudioEffect#EFFECT_AUXILIARY or AudioEffect#EFFECT_PRE_PROCESSING
  • name: human readable effect name
  • implementor: human readable effect implementor name

The method AudioEffect#queryEffects() returns an array of AudioEffectDescriptors to facilitate effects enumeration.

gaia::base::String gaia::media::AudioEffectDescriptor::connectMode ( )

Indicates if the effect is of insert category AudioEffect#EFFECT_INSERT, auxiliary category AudioEffect#EFFECT_AUXILIARY or pre processing category AudioEffect#EFFECT_PRE_PROCESSING.

Insert effects (Typically an Equalizer) are applied to the entire audio source and usually not shared by several sources. Auxiliary effects (typically a reverberator) are applied to part of the signal (wet) and the effect output is added to the original signal (dry). Audio pre processing are applied to audio captured on a particular AudioRecord.

gaia::base::String gaia::media::AudioEffectDescriptor::type ( )

Indicates the generic type of the effect (Equalizer, Bass boost ...).

The UUID corresponds to the OpenSL ES Interface ID for this type of effect.

gaia::base::String gaia::media::AudioEffectDescriptor::uuid ( )

Indicates the particular implementation of the effect in that type.

Several effects can have the same type but this uuid is unique to a given implementation.
